{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6bddc974-4530-47c3-bce9-d721ba498446","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n### Authentication Options (`--auth`)\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (org accounts) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n### Examples\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain contoso.onmicrosoft.com --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C --domain contoso.b2clogin.com\n\n# Windows auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows\n```\n\n### Other useful flags\n- `--use-controllers` — use controllers instead of minimal APIs\n- `--use-program-main` — use explicit `Main` method\n- `--no-openapi` — disable OpenAPI/Swagger support\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` for the full list of options.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"987822c5-57e6-4ecd-9a1c-8426c14dd62c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":359,"requestId":"5024:18EC0:12D84C2:1532862:6A066E7C"},"id":"2d7d9d35-243a-40cd-8508-34b0adbb21f6","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:29.082Z","parentId":"819d6e2d-53f6-4d02-a57b-e925743e100c"}
